%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22An%20East%20Coast%20restaurant%20chain%20has%20been%20ordered%20to%20pay%20%2411.4%20million%20back%20to%20more%20than%201%2C300%20employees%20over%20claims%20it%20paid%20staff%20below%20minimum%20wage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Close-up%20of%20chefs%20hands%20holding%20a%20saute%20pan%20to%20cook%20food%2C%20flambeing%20contents.%20Flames%20rising%20from%20the%20pan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654e0c913cc84b4dfaffe6dd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMint%20Images%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20East%20Coast%20restaurant%20chain%20failed%20to%20pay%20minimum%20wages%20and%20overtime%20rates%20to%20some%20workers%2C%20the%20Labor%20Department%20says.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20DOL%20said%20some%20restaurants%20paid%20set%20wages%20regardless%20of%20hours%20worked%2C%20which%20could%20reach%2065%20a%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPlaza%20Azteca%20has%20been%20ordered%20to%C2%A0pay%20%2411.4%20million%20back%20to%20more%20than%201%2C300%20affected%20employees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20restaurant%20chain%20with%20dozens%20of%20locations%20on%20the%20East%20Coast%20has%20been%20ordered%20to%20pay%20%2411.4%20million%20back%20to%20more%20than%201%2C300%20employees%20after%20a%20federal%20agency%20uncovered%20a%20series%20of%20apparent%20labor-law%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20include%20Plaza%20Azteca%20failing%20to%20pay%20minimum%20wages%20and%20overtime%20rates%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor%20said.%20A%20consent%20judgment%20said%20that%20the%20chain%20admitted%20to%20violating%20sections%20of%20the%20Fair%20Labor%20Standards%20Act%20related%20to%20minimum%20wages%2C%20maximum%20hours%2C%20and%20collection%20of%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Labor%20first%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20the%20Mexican%20chain%20in%20September%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%20claimed%20that%20numerous%20Plaza%20Azteca%20restaurants%20paid%20predetermined%20amounts%20to%20back-of-the-house%20employees%2C%20like%20bussers%2C%20cooks%2C%20and%20dishwashers%2C%20regardless%20of%20how%20many%20hours%20they%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20meant%20that%20the%20employers%20failed%20to%20pay%20the%20minimum%20wage%20to%20some%20employees%20and%20didn't%20pay%20a%20time-and-a-half%20rate%20pay%20to%20some%20employees%20for%20hours%20worked%20over%2040%20in%20a%20workweek%2C%20the%20DOL%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20back-of-the-house%20employees%20at%20the%20company's%20restaurants%20worked%20between%2056%20and%2065%20hours%20per%20workweek%2C%20and%20in%20some%20weeks%20this%20brought%20their%20hourly%20pay%20down%20to%20just%20%243%2C%20the%20DOL%20alleged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20restaurant%20also%20created%20%26quot%3Bfalse%26quot%3B%20payroll%20records%20claiming%20that%20staff%20received%20overtime%20premiums%2C%20the%20DOL's%20suit%20said.%20Some%20workers%20were%20also%20kept%20%26quot%3Boff%20the%20books%26quot%3B%20entirely%2C%20the%20DOL%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20some%20of%20the%20restaurants%2C%20the%20company%20also%20failed%20to%20pay%20%26quot%3Bany%20cash%20wages%20whatsoever%26quot%3B%20to%20some%20servers%20who%20were%20forced%20to%20work%20for%20tips%20only%20and%20also%20seized%20a%20proportion%20of%20their%20tips%2C%20the%20DOL%20said%20in%20the%20lawsuit.%20It%20said%20that%20the%20chain%20%26quot%3Bstole%20hard-earned%20wages%20and%20tips%20from%20hundreds%20of%20employees%26quot%3B%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Plaza%20Azteca's%20initial%20answer%20to%20the%20complaint%2C%20in%20October%202022%2C%20it%20denied%20the%20allegations%20and%20said%20it%20didn't%20have%20any%20policies%20that%20meant%20staff%20worked%20uncompensated%20time%2C%20including%20overtime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20restaurant%20agreed%20to%20a%20consent%20judgment%20this%20September%20%26quot%3Bafter%20months%20of%20litigation%20and%20just%20before%20a%20jury%20trial%20was%20scheduled%20to%20begin%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20DOL%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dol.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Freleases%2Fwhd%2Fwhd20231109%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dol.gov%2Fsites%2Fdolgov%2Ffiles%2FOPA%2Fnewsreleases%2F2023%2F11%2FWHD20232039NAT%2520_%2520Amended%2520Consent%2520Judgment%2520Order%2520Plaza%2520Azteca.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsent%20judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20accompanying%20press%20release%20don't%20refer%20to%20the%20DOL's%20claims%20that%20the%20restaurants%20failed%20to%20pay%20cash%20wages%20to%20some%20servers%20and%20also%20took%20a%20proportion%20of%20their%20tips.%20Insider%20has%20contacted%20the%20DOL%20for%20further%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20consent%20judgment%2C%20the%20restaurant%20agreed%20to%20pay%20%245.7%20million%20in%20back%20wages%20and%20the%20same%20amount%20in%20liquidated%20damages%20to%20a%20total%20of%201%2C320%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20related%20to%20contraventions%20that%20occurred%20between%20March%202016%20and%20September%202021%20at%20restaurants%20in%20Connecticut%2C%20Maryland%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20Pennsylvania%20and%20Virginia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20consent%20judgment%20also%20included%20%24625%2C000%20in%20civil%20money%20penalties%2C%20which%20the%20DOL%20said%20was%20due%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Brepeat%20and%20wilful%20nature%20of%20the%20violations.%26quot%3B%20Including%20interest%2C%20the%20restaurant%20is%20set%20to%20pay%20a%20total%20of%20around%20%2412%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20did%20not%20immediately%20receive%20a%20response%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20to%20Plaza%20Azteca%20outside%20regular%20US%20working%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2