ay%20came%20down%20hard%20on%20both%20Punjab%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%20governors%20after%20the%20state%20governments%20accused%20them%20of%20delaying%20action%20on%20bills%20cleared%20by%20the%20assemblies.%20The%20bench%2C%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20urged%20both%20the%20governors%20to%20not%20delay%20the%20bills%20that%20have%20been%20cleared%20by%20the%20elected%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlease%20don't%20deflect%20the%20course%20of%20bills%20passed%20by%20a%20duly%20elected%20assembly.%20It's%20a%20matter%20of%20very%20serious%20concern%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20playing%20with%20fire.%20How%20can%20the%20governor%20say%20this%3F%20We%20are%20not%20happy%20with%20what%20is%20happening%20in%20Punjab.%20Will%20we%20continue%20to%20be%20a%20parliamentary%20democracy%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20added%20while%20emphasising%20that%20India%20has%20been%20running%20on%20established%20traditions%20and%20conventions%20and%20they%20need%20to%20be%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Punjab%20government%20had%20earlier%20moved%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20alleging%20delay%20in%20Governor%20Banwarilal%20Purohit's%20giving%20assent%20to%20bills%20passed%20by%20the%20state%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plea%20said%20such%20%26quot%3Bunconstitutional%20inaction%26quot%3B%20has%20brought%20the%20entire%20administration%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bgrinding%20halt.%26quot%3B%20Senior%20advocate%20Abhishek%20Singhvi%2C%20arguing%20for%20the%20Punjab%20government%2C%20had%20said%20the%20governor%20had%20kept%20back%20seven%20bills%20including%20those%20related%20to%20fiscal%20management%20and%20education.%20He%20said%20the%20bills%20were%20sent%20for%20the%20governor's%20nod%20in%20July%20and%20his%20inaction%20has%20affected%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20has%20directed%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20to%20place%20on%20record%20the%20details%20of%20ac