c%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654ddf1536d588dc55ce40e4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20during%20joint%20press%20conference%20with%20President%20of%20the%20European%20Commission%20Ursula%20von%20der%20Leyen%20on%20November%204%2C%202023%20in%20Kyiv%2C%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EViktor%20Kovalchuk%2FGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUkrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20has%20an%2081%25%20approval%20rating%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Gallup%20poll.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20he's%20declared%20that%20Ukraine%20won't%20hold%20a%20wartime%20election.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20election%20in%20the%20near%20future%20would%20be%20disastrous%20for%20Ukraine's%20democracy%2C%20experts%20say.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20announced%20that%20he%20wouldn't%20support%20elections%20while%20Kyiv%20is%20at%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20statement%20put%20to%20rest%20questions%20that%20arose%20when%20foreign%20allies%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lgraham.senate.gov%2Fpublic%2Findex.cfm%2F2023%2F8%2Fgraham-on-ukraine-president-supporting-democratic-elections-in-2024%23%3A~%3Atext%3DI%2520cannot%2520think%2520of%2520a%2Cembrace%2520of%2520democracy%2520and%2520freedom.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESouth%20Carolina%20Sen.%20Lindsey%20Graham%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20suggested%20Ukraine%20hit%20the%20polls%20amid%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Ukrainian%20president's%20speech%20on%20Monday%20was%20loud%20and%20clear%3A%20no%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20must%20realize%20that%20now%20is%20the%20time%20of%20defense%2C%20the%20time%20of%20battle%20that%20determines%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20state%20and%20people%2C%20not%20the%20time%20of%20manipulations%2C%20which%20only%20Russia%20expects%20from%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20believe%20that%20now%20is%20not%20the%20right%20time%20for%20elections.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folena-zelenksa-zelenskyy-ukraine-presidential-election-war-martial-law-democracy-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelection%20in%20the%20near%20future%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20technically%20be%20great%20for%20Zelenskyy%2C%20who%20holds%20a%20staggering%2081%25%20personal%20approval%20rating%20in%20Ukraine.%20That's%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F512258%2Fukrainians-stand-behind-war-effort-despite-fatigue.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20Gallup%20public%20opinion%20poll%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20on%20October%209.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20experts%20on%20wartime%20politics%20and%20a%20Ukrainian%20election%20watchdog%20said%20Zelenskyy's%20decision%20to%20delay%20the%20election%20makes%20sense.%20War%20should%20be%20the%20focus%2C%20and%20holding%20an%20election%20now%20would%20undermine%20Ukraine's%20democracy%20instead%20of%20upholding%20it%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BElections%20and%20war%20are%20incompatible%2C%26quot%3B%20Opora%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20civil%20society%20that%20monitors%20elections%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20examined%20three%20key%20questions%20relating%20to%20Ukraine's%20wartime%20election%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECan%20Zelenskyy%20delay%20or%20call%20for%20an%20election%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENo%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.refworld.org%2Fpdfid%2F44a280124.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkrainian%20constitution%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcvk.gov.ua%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2FElection-Code-of-Ukraine.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelectoral%20code%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20the%20president%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20Zelenskyy%20has%20neither%20the%20power%20to%20cancel%20elections%20nor%20call%20them.%20That%20authority%20rests%20with%20the%20Ukrainian%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20country%20is%20currently%20under%20martial%20law%2C%20which%20prohibits%20the%20holding%20of%20elections%20and%20all%20political%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZelenskyy%20was%20clear%20about%20this%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F05%2F13%2Fzelensky-washington-post-interview-transcript%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMay%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20The%20Washington%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20have%20martial%20law%2C%20we%20cannot%20have%20elections%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20constitution%20prohibits%20any%20elections%20during%20martial%20law.%20If%20there%20is%20no%20martial%20law%2C%20then%20there%20will%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20leadership%20must%20extend%20martial%20law%20every%2090%20days%2C%20and%20Zelenskyy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rferl.org%2Fa%2Fukraine-zelenskiy-martial-law-mobilization-russia%2F32678119.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejust%20signed%20bills%3C%2Fa%3E%20extending%20martial%20law%20until%20February%2014%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZelenskyy%2C%20who%20was%20elected%20in%20March%202019%2C%20would%20have%20been%20set%20to%20bid%20for%20reelection%20in%20a%20presidential%20race%20early%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOf%20course%2C%20everyone%20understands%20that%20a%20range%20of%20civil%20rights%20are%20legally%20limited%20when%20martial%20law%20is%20imposed%2C%26quot%3B%20Opora%20said.%20Under%20martial%20law%2C%20people%20can't%20hold%20mass%20gatherings%20like%20political%20rallies%20and%20have%20to%20abide%20by%20curfews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20such%20restrictions%20are%20necessary%20in%20the%20warring%20country%2C%20and%20similar%20legal%20norms%20exist%20in%20many%20democratic%20states%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20civil%20society%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20is%20Ukraine%20delaying%20the%20election%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%2C%20most%20Ukrainians%20don't%20want%20an%20election%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20have%20been%20nine%20surveys%20now%20where%20the%20public%20has%20in%20representative%20samples%20been%20asked%20whether%20they%20want%20elections%20during%20the%20war%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkiis.com.ua%2F%3Flang%3Dukr%26cat%3Dreports%26id%3D1309%26page%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E65%20to%2080%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20clearly%20answered%20that%20they%20cannot%20see%20elections%20happening%20during%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20Peter%20Erben%2C%20Ukraine%20country%20director%20for%20The%20International%20Foundation%20for%20Electoral%20Systems%2C%20or%20IFES%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DuJmIe2C2i5o%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20on%20October%2026.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20should%20listen%20to%20the%20Ukrainian%20public%20in%20this%20regard%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20100%20Ukrainian%20NGOs%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oporaua.org%2Fen%2Fvybory%2Fover-100-csos-urge-not-to-have-elections-during-the-war-24905%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esigned%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20saying%20a%20wartime%20election%20is%20not%20feasible.%20The%20appeal%2C%20led%20by%20Opora%2C%20warned%20that%20%26quot%3Belections%20during%20the%20active%20phase%20of%20the%20war%20are%20extremely%20dangerous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20country%20under%20martial%20law%20has%20little%20room%20for%20opposition%20campaigning%20or%20fair%20political%20media%20coverage%2C%20Opora%20told%20Insider.%20And%20with%20a%20war%20ongoing%20and%20millions%20of%20Ukrainians%20displaced%2C%20a%20significant%20number%20of%20voters%20won't%20show%20up%20to%20the%20polls%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20turn%2C%20the%20president%20would%20obviously%20be%20able%20to%20win%20the%20election%20now%20given%20the%20high%20level%20of%20support%2C%20but%20if%20there%20is%20no%20secure%20process%20on%20voting%20day%2C%20the%20low%20turnout%20will%20delegitimize%20the%20government%20as%20a%20whole%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20civil%20group%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20wartime%20election%20in%20Ukraine%20would%20also%20be%20rare%2C%20if%20not%20unprecedented%2C%20in%20modern%20Europe%2C%20Helmut%20Norpoth%2C%20a%20professor%20emeritus%20at%20Stony%20Brook%20University's%20department%20of%20political%20science%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLogic%20would%20probably%20dictate%2C%20even%20in%20a%20democracy%2C%20to%20postpone%20an%20election%2C%20which%20is%20sort%20of%20inherently%20divisive%20and%20partisan%20when%20you're%20trying%20to%20fight%20external%20enemies%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Norpoth%2C%20whose%20work%20focuses%20on%20elections%20and%20wartime%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20all%20modern%20democracies%20have%20delayed%20elections%20when%20enemy%20troops%20are%20on%20their%20soil%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20major%20exception%20in%20the%20world%2C%20Norpoth%20said%2C%20has%20been%20the%20US%2C%20which%20held%20elections%20during%20significant%20conflicts%20like%20the%20Civil%20War%2C%20the%20War%20of%201812%2C%20and%20World%20War%20II.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20would%20a%20wartime%20election%20look%20like%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Ukraine%20did%20move%20forward%20with%20a%20wartime%20election%2C%20it%20would%20face%20a%20laundry%20list%20of%20serious%20challenges%2C%20the%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EErben%20and%20Gio%20Kobakhidze%2C%20Ukraine%20deputy%20country%20director%20for%20IFES%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlanticcouncil.org%2Fblogs%2Fukrainealert%2Fwhat-would-it-take-to-hold-elections-in-ukraine%2F%26sa%3DD%26source%3Ddocs%26ust%3D1699599231907857%26usg%3DAOvVaw1SavkgLcQjG6AftUeVF8PB%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20in%20September%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20in%20order%20for%20a%20wartime%20election%20to%20happen%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20number%20of%20preconditions%20must%20be%20met%20that%20are%20currently%20absent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20major%20requirement%20is%20that%20Ukraine%20has%20to%20somehow%20provide%20voting%20access%20to%20its%20active%20troops%2C%20of%20which%20there%20are%20more%20than%201%20million%2C%20and%20nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.unhcr.org%2Fen%2Fsituations%2Fukraine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E6%20million%20refugees%20overseas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrefugees.org%2Femergencies%2Fukraine%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E5%20million%20other%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20internally%20displaced%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElections%20are%20also%20expensive%2C%20Opora%20said%2C%20in%20a%20time%20when%20Ukraine%20needs%20money%20for%20weapons%2C%20humanitarian%20aid%2C%20and%20medical%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVoting%20infrastructure%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20also%20been%20devastated%20by%20the%20war%2C%20with%20buildings%20for%20polling%20stations%20such%20as%20schools%20and%20hospitals%20destroyed%2C%20Opora%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20are%20the%20areas%20near%20the%20frontlines%2C%20where%20voters%20gathering%20en%20masse%20to%20cast%20their%20ballots%20could%20easily%20be%20targeted%20by%20a%20Russian%20strike%20%E2%80%94%20a%20problem%20when%20Ukrainians%20overwhelmingly%20want%20to%20vote%20in%20person%2C%20the%20civil%20society%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20electronic%20voting%20system%20cannot%20be%20used%20in%20the%20conditions%20when%20Russia%20interferes%20in%20elections%20around%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Opora%20said.%20%26quot%3BOnly%208%25%20of%20citizens%20trust%20postal%20voting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Ukraine%20would%20also%20have%20to%20consider%20how%20it%20would%20provide%20access%20to%20its%20citizens%20in%20occupied%20areas%20of%20Russia%2C%20Norpoth%20said.%20Moscow%20holds%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2022%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fukraine-maps.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E20%25%20of%20Ukraine's%20territory.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20probably%20will%20not%20send%20any%20ballots%20to%20areas%20occupied%20by%20Russia%2C%20which%20is%20a%20little%20bit%20like%20what%20happened%20with%20the%20Civil%20War%2C%26quot%3B%20Norpoth%20said.%20%26quot%3BThose%20residents%20will%20probably%20not%20have%20a%20chance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20Erben%20and%20Kobakhidze%20wrote%2C%20Ukraine's%20laws%20correctly%20recognize%20that%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20wartime%20election%20is%20implausible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20they%20also%20emphasized%20that%20Ukraine%20should%20hold%20an%20election%20after%20the%20war%20and%20improve%20on%20voting%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpora%20concurred.%20%26quot%3BNow%20Ukraine%20has%20to%20act%20the%20same%20way%20as%20any%20other%20Western%20democracy%20would%20do%20under%20the%20conditions%20of%20full-scale%20war%20%E2%80%94%20impose%20martial%20law%20and%20postpone%20certain%20processes%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZelenskyy%20had%20harsh%20words%20on%20Monday%20for%20anyone%20urging%20Ukraine%20to%20hold%20a%20wartime%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20all%20understand%20that%20now%2C%20in%20wartime%2C%20when%20there%20are%20so%20many%20challenges%2C%20it%20is%20absolutely%20irresponsible%20to%20throw%20the%20topic%20of%20elections%20into%20society%20in%20a%20lighthearted%20and%20playful%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-election-wartime-delay-volodymyr-zelenskyy-martial-law-analysis-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699612854000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654e0656b788914e5553c24a%3Fformat%3Dj