0capable%20of%20being%20served%20because%20anyone%20who%20tried%20to%20approach%20him%20would%20be%20tackled%20by%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrimes'%20lawyers%20said%20in%20the%20supplemental%20proof%20of%20service%20that%20Musk%20was%20served%20via%20substitute%20service%20on%20October%2020%2C%20and%20that%20they%20also%20mailed%20the%20custody%20papers%20to%20him%20on%20that%20date%20too.%20Melcher%20said%20typically%20Musk%20would%20be%20required%20to%20respond%2010%20days%20after%20the%20substitute%20service%2C%20plus%20the%20typical%2030%20days%2C%20meaning%20he%20would%20have%20until%20November%2029.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelcher%20added%20that%20another%20reason%20the%20date%20of%20service%20matters%20is%20because%20the%20standing%20order%20that%20prevents%20the%20children%20from%20being%20moved%20out%20of%20California%20does%20not%20apply%20to%20Musk%20until%20he%20is%20served.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20step%20for%20Musk%20will%20likely%20be%20to%20file%20a%20motion%20arguing%20the%20custody%20case%20should%20go%20forward%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-grimes-texas-better-california-rich-child-support-fight-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETexas%2C%20where%20he%20sued%20Grimes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rather%20than%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20will%20be%20in%20legal%20limbo%20for%20months%20until%20the%20jurisdictional%20dispute%20is%20resolved%2C%26quot%3B%20Melcher%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20and%20lawyers%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-grimes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMusk%20and%20Grimes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20requests%20for%20comment%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pair%20were%20in%20an%20off-and-on%20again%20relationship%20that%20started%20in%202018.%20The%20couple%20first%20broke%20up%20in%202021%2C%20but%20they%20contin