itle%22%3A%2218-year-old%20in%20love%20with%20minor%20killed%20by%20girl%E2%80%99s%20kin%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699584701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105111202%2Cimgsize-24892.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhyderabad%2F18-year-old-in-love-with-minor-killed-by-girls-kin%2Farticleshow%2F105108984.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%2018-year-old%20truck%20cleaner%20was%20killed%20by%20the%20family%20members%20of%20a%20minor%20girl%20he%20was%20allegedly%20in%20love%20with.%20The%20accused%20attacked%20him%20with%20sticks%20and%20poured%20chilli%20powder%20on%20his%20private%20parts.%20The%20victim%20was%20declared%20dead%20at%20the%20hospital.%20Eight%20suspects%20have%20been%20taken%20into%20custody.%20The%20victim's%20mother%20claimed%20that%20the%20girl's%20family%20had%20threatened%20to%20kill%20him%20if%20he%20continued%20the%20friendship.%20The%20police%20have%20registered%20a%20case%20and%20assured%20a%20thorough%20investigation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TNN%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20lice%20evolved%20alongside%20humans%20to%20become%20the%20perfect%20pests%20%E2%80%94%20and%20trackers%20of%20human%20migration%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225297%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Close-up%20of%20a%20head%20louse.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654c26893cc84b4dfaff19de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223489%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EClose-up%20of%20a%20head%20louse.%3Cp%3EOxford%20Scientific%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHead%20lice%20have%20plagued%20communities%20for%20centuries%20across%20the%20world.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20have%20evolved%20%E2%80%94%20and%20traveled%20%E2%80%94%20with%20humans%20to%20continually%20survive%20and%20find%20new%20hosts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20a%20new%20study%20suggests%20lice%20DNA%20can%20help%20track%20human%20migration%20from%20continent%20to%20continent.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20humans%20have%20had%20hair%2C%20we've%20probably%20also%20had%20lice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20small%20parasites%2C%20which%20live%20on%20human%20heads%2C%20have%20plagued%20school%20classrooms%20and%20sleepovers%20alike%20for%20centuries%2C%20but%20a%20new%20study%20shows%20a%20previously%20undiscovered%20good%20side%20to%20them%20%E2%80%94%20their%20DNA%20could%20hold%20answers%20to%20human%20migratory%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarina%20Ascunce%2C%20who%20works%20as%20an%20evolutionary%20geneticist%20at%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fgoatsandsoda%2F2023%2F11%2F08%2F1211528184%2Fhaving-lice-aint-nice-but-they-tell-our-story-concise-and-precise%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20NPR%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20lice%20were%20like%20%26quot%3Bheirlooms%20of%20our%20past.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAscunce%20and%20her%20colleagues%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.plos.org%2Fplosone%2Farticle%3Fid%3D10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0293409%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20a%20study%20in%20PLOS%20One%20%3C%2Fa%3Erevealing%20their%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20complete%20the%20study%2C%20the%20researchers%20looked%20at%20175%20head%20lice%20from%2018%20sampling%20locations%20and%20nine%20geographic%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20found%20that%20two%20different%20genetic%20clusters%20were%20present%20in%20the%20lice's%20DNA%2C%20which%20indicated%20that%20head%20lice%20came%20to%20the%20Americas%20two%20separate%20times%2C%20per%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Ascunce%2C%20the%20findings%20suggest%20that%20the%20lice%20were%20first%20brought%20to%20the%20Americas%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20humans%20crossed%20the%20Bering%20Strait%20from%20Asia%20into%20North%20America%2C%20per%20NPR.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20around%20the%2016th%20century%2C%20European%20colonizers%20brought%20their%20own%20head%20lice%20to%20the%20Americas%20when%20they%20arrived%2C%20according%20to%20NPR.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20lice%20are%20mirroring%20the%20colonization%20of%20the%20Americas%2C%26quot%3B%20Ascunce%20told%20NPR.%20%26quot%3BThe%20two%20migration%20waves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20also%20suggested%2C%20per%20its%20conclusion%2C%20that%20the%20distinction%20between%20the%20clusters%20could%20be%20a%20result%20of%20some%20kind%20of%20internal%20mechanism%20preventing%20the%20lice%20from%20genetically%20intermixing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20specialist%2C%20invertebrate%20biologist%20Alejandra%20Perotti%2C%20told%20NPR%20the%20study%20had%20a%20good%20approach%2C%20but%20shouldn't%20be%20considered%20conclusive%20due%20to%20its%20small%20sampling%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20data%20they%20gather%2C%20some%20of%20the%20populations%20have%20only%20one%20louse%2C%20including%20Africa%2C%20for%20example%2C%26quot%3B%20Perotti%20said%20to%20NPR.%20%26quot%3BSo%20there%20is%20an%20issue%20with%20the%20sampling%20size.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20to%20worry%20%E2%80%94%20Ascunce%20and%20her%20fellow%20researchers%20are%20already%20planning%20further%20studies%2C%20per%20NPR%2C%20where%20they%20plan%20to%20look%20for%20potential%20louse%20interactions%20between%20early%20humans%20and%20Neanderthals%2C%20who%20would%20have%20also%20had%20lice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flice-louse-head-evolution-hair-pests-migration-human-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699584391000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654c26b13cc84b4dfaff19ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flice