26quot%3BIf%20they%20were%20gone%2C%20it%20wouldn't%20affect%20us%20in%20any%20negative%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20report%20estimated%20that%20since%201600%2C%20rats%20introduced%20to%20islands%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs10530-012-0351-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecaused%20between%2040%25%20to%2060%25%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20all%20reptile%20and%20bird%20extinctions.%20With%20abundant%20garbage%20available%20to%20them%2C%20city%20rats%20might%20not%20go%20after%20wildlife%20in%20the%20same%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20all%20rats%20in%20NYC%20died%20tomorrow%20it%20would%20still%20save%20a%20lot%20of%20animals%20like%20birds%2C%20coyotes%2C%20foxes%2C%20and%20feral%20cats%20that%20die%20each%20year%20from%20rodenticide%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-hiring-bloodthirsty-director-rodent-mitigation-fight-rats-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoison%20used%20to%20kill%20rats%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Munshi-South%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByers%20agreed%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20big%20problems%20is%20that%20the%20poison%20just%20doesn't%20stay%20in%20the%20rats%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20ends%20up%20in%20the%20animals%20that%20feed%20on%20the%20rats%2C%20like%20the%20predatory%20birds%20or%20other%20urban%20wildlife%20that%20eat%20those%20animals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20rat%20leaves%20its%20burrow%20in%20a%20park%20in%20New%20York%20City%20in%202015.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6408d95d1bbdd30018ed7c09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20rat%20leaves%20its%20burrow%20in%20a%20park%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20possibly%20to%20go%20hunt%20down%20some%20fresh%20garbage.%3Cp%3EMary%20Altaffer%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20scav